            "strDescription": "Layered basmati rice with spiced chicken — the celebratory dish of homes across Pakistan. Dum (steam) finishes the pot so every grain carries aroma from whole spices, fried onions, and yogurt-marinated chicken.",
            "strInstructions": "1. Wash and soak basmati 30 minutes; drain.\n2. Marinate chicken 1–2 hours: yogurt, ginger-garlic, red chilli, turmeric, biryani masala, half the fried onions, lemon.\n3. In a heavy pot, heat ghee/oil; add whole spices (bay, cardamom, cloves, cinnamon). Sauté sliced onions until golden; reserve some for garnish.\n4. Add marinated chicken; bhunofy on medium-high until oil separates and chicken is nearly cooked.\n5. Boil rice in salted water with green cardamom until 70% cooked; drain.\n6. Layer: chicken masala → rice → saffron milk (optional) → mint, coriander, remaining fried onions. Seal lid with cloth or tight seal.\n7. Dum on low 18–22 minutes. Rest 10 minutes off heat before opening.\n8. Gently fork through; serve with raita and salad.",
            "ingredients": [{
                    "ingredient": "Basmati rice",
                    "measure": "500g"
                },
                {
                    "ingredient": "Chicken (bone-in)",
                    "measure": "800g"
                },
                {
                    "ingredient": "Plain yogurt",
                    "measure": "200g"
                },
                {
                    "ingredient": "Onions (sliced, fried)",
                    "measure": "3 large"
                },
                {
                    "ingredient": "Ginger-garlic paste",
                    "measure": "3 tbsp"
                },
                {
                    "ingredient": "Biryani masala",
                    "measure": "3 tbsp"
                },
